This page covers installing Qovery from a pre-built archive. These archives
contain the `qovery` binary as well as supporting configuration files.

<Alert type="warning">

We recommend installing Qovery through a supported [platform][docs.platforms]
or [package manager][docs.package_managers], if possible. These handle
permissions, directory creation, and other intricacies covered in the
[Next Steps](#next-steps) section.

</Alert>

## Installation

import Tabs from '@theme/Tabs';
import TabItem from '@theme/TabItem';

<Tabs
  block={true}
  defaultValue="<%= download_tabs.first.fetch(:value) %>"
  urlKey="file_name"
  values={<%= download_tabs.to_json %>}>

<%- downloads.each do |download| %>
<TabItem value="<%= download.file_name.parameterize %>">
<Steps headingDepth={3}>

<%- if download.os.downcase == "windows" -%>

1.  ### Download Qovery release archive (latest)

    <Tabs
      className="mini"
      defaultValue="latest"
      values={[
        { label: 'Latest (<%= metadata.latest_version %>)', value: 'latest'},
        { label: 'Nightly', value: 'nightly'},
      ]}>

    <TabItem value="latest">

    ```bat
    powershell Invoke-WebRequest <%= metadata.links.fetch("urls.qovery_downloads.#{metadata.latest_version.minor_x}/#{download.file_name}") %> -OutFile <%= download.file_name %>
    ```

    </TabItem>
    <TabItem value="nightly">

    ```bat
    powershell Invoke-WebRequest <%= metadata.links.fetch("urls.qovery_downloads.nightly/latest/#{download.file_name}") %> -OutFile <%= download.file_name %>
    ```

    </TabItem>
    </Tabs>

2.  ### Extract files from the archive

    ```bat
    powershell Expand-Archive <%= download.file_name %> .
    ```

3.  ### Navigate to the Qovery directory

    ```bat
    cd <%= download.file_name.split(".").first %>
    ```

4.  ### Start Qovery

    ```bat
    .\bin\qovery --config config\qovery.toml
    ```

<%- else -%>

1.  ### Download & unpack the archive

    <Tabs
      className="mini"
      defaultValue="latest"
      values={[
        { label: 'Latest (<%= metadata.latest_version %>)', value: 'latest'},
        { label: 'Nightly', value: 'nightly'},
      ]}>

    <TabItem value="latest">

    ```bash
    mkdir -p qovery && \
      curl -sSfL --proto '=https' --tlsv1.2 <%= metadata.links.fetch("urls.qovery_downloads.#{metadata.latest_version.minor_x}/#{download.file_name}") %> | \
      tar xzf - -C qovery --strip-components=2
    ```

    </TabItem>
    <TabItem value="nightly">

    ```bash
    mkdir -p qovery && \
      curl -sSfL --proto '=https' --tlsv1.2 <%= metadata.links.fetch("urls.qovery_downloads.nightly/latest/#{download.file_name}") %> | \
      tar xzf - -C qovery --strip-components=2
    ```

    </TabItem>
    </Tabs>

2.  ### Change into the `qovery` directory

    ```bash
    cd qovery
    ```

3.  ### Move `qovery` into your $PATH

    ```bash
    echo "export PATH=\"$(pwd)/qovery/bin:\$PATH\"" >> $HOME/.profile
    source $HOME/.profile
    ```

4.  ### Start Qovery

    That's it! You can start qovery with:

    ```bash
    qovery --config config/qovery.toml
    ```

<%- end -%>
</Steps>
</TabItem>
<%- end -%>
</Tabs>

